# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FRONTEND PRODUCTION ENV TEMPLATE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `frontend/.env.production` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Vite reads this file automatically when building with `vite build` (or
# any time `import.meta.env.MODE === "production"`). Values are baked into
# the bundle at build time — rebuilding is required after any change.
#
# All values here are PUBLIC: the anon key is designed to be shipped in the
# browser bundle. The real secret is the JWT signing key, which lives on
# Supabase and is never exposed to this layer.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase project API URL. Find at:
#   Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API → "Project URL"
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://<your-project-ref>.supabase.co

# Publishable (anon) key. Find at:
#   Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API → "anon public"
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your-anon-key>
